# GitHub Linguist overrides — keep the language-stat bar honest.
#
# GitHub computes the language percentages on the public repo page (smol.unityailab.com /
# Unity-Lab-AI/Starship-Made-of-Lies) by walking every committed file and bucketing by
# extension via `github-linguist`. Without overrides the legacy UMS reference dump in
# `_ums-reference/references/{mdk2,modapi,pbapi}/` (30,454 third-party Space Engineers HTML
# documentation files preserved per the "we nuke nothing but track it all" rule until
# PHASE 15) dominates the stats and makes the repo look ~98% HTML.
#
# The active SMoL project is TypeScript + React + CSS. These attributes tell linguist:
#   - `linguist-vendored`     → excluded from stats entirely (treated as vendor/third-party)
#   - `linguist-documentation`→ also excluded; flagged as reference docs not source
#   - `linguist-generated`    → also excluded; flagged as generated/transformed output
#
# Stacking all three is belt-and-suspenders — any one of them excludes the path. Linguist
# re-runs on every push; the public-repo language bar updates within a few minutes of the
# next push to main.

# === UMS-era reference material (Space Engineers Mod API + PB Scripting API + MDK2 docs) ===
# Third-party HTML docs preserved as reference until PHASE 15 (UMS nuke). Excluded from
# stats because they're external documentation, not project source code.
_ums-reference/**           linguist-vendored linguist-documentation linguist-generated

# === Build / dist output (if ever committed by accident) ===
client/dist/**              linguist-generated
server/dist/**              linguist-generated
shared/dist/**              linguist-generated
**/node_modules/**          linguist-vendored

# === Lock files + minified bundles ===
pnpm-lock.yaml              linguist-generated
package-lock.json           linguist-generated
*.min.js                    linguist-generated
*.min.css                   linguist-generated
*.map                       linguist-generated

# === Line endings — keep Windows-friendly auto-CRLF for the few legacy files that need it,
#     but force LF on every source extension so cross-platform team (Gee/Red/Sponge/Alfreddo)
#     doesn't end up with churn from line-ending diffs on every commit.
*.ts                        text eol=lf
*.tsx                       text eol=lf
*.js                        text eol=lf
*.cjs                       text eol=lf
*.mjs                       text eol=lf
*.css                       text eol=lf
*.json                      text eol=lf
*.md                        text eol=lf
*.html                      text eol=lf
*.yml                       text eol=lf
*.yaml                      text eol=lf
